{
  "texts": [
    "This work showcases the use of highvolume structured databases for automatically verifying novel claims.",
    "Expanding beyond our pilot datasets to large-scale collections of claims and corresponding evidence from structured sources remains an important next step.",
    "Despite the advancements made in this study, our system's limitations should be acknowledged.",
    "While this study focuses primarily on improving evidence retrieval, it does not comprehensively evaluate different fact verification approaches.",
    "Fact verification is critical for automatic fact-checking, and a deeper investigation into various verification strategies, including fine-tuned models and LLMbased approaches, could further enhance system performance."
  ]
}